ğŸ¥” Accordion Potatoes ğŸ“ Recipe 1-2 Potato Water 1 tsp â€¢ Salt 1 tsp â€¢ Baking Soda Oil Dried Parsley Chili Sauce Steps: â€¢ Cutting the Potato - Peel off the potato - Cut the ends of potato - Cut the potato lengthwise / just like shown in my video, however you like and based on the size of the potato - Take 2 skewers - Put the potato horizontally and place the skewers on both sides of the potato - Cut the potato in vertical lines - Flip the potato - Cut the potato again in diagonal lines â€¢ Soaking; Accordion Potatoes - Prepare water with salt and baking soda - Soak the accordion potatoes in water for 5-10 minutes - After soaking the potatoes, dry them with tissue / towel â€¢ Cooking; Accordion Potatoes - Heat the oil in pan at medium heat - Fry the accordion potatoes until crispy and golden brown â€¢ Finishing; Accordion Potatoes - Serve the potato with dried parsley and chili sauce Tips: 1.
